He sent Rachel and Chris E. up to investigate locally; after removing and reinserting all the keys, the keybank read COMPLETE. We suspect the key sense shaft didn't quite reset properly when they returned their key after leaving the manway alcove. However, since they had to leave the LI18/19 boundary gate unguarded in order to investigate the keybank upstairs, the LI18 search was no longer valid and we needed to restart. The interlock checks are already complete so we shouldn't lose too much time.
